definitions: constituting number one million in a sequence; 1,000,000th

examples.text: the museum welcomed its millionth visitor 21 months after opening

shortDefinitions: constituting number one million in sequence

definitions: constituting an unspecified but very large number in a sequence

examples.text: I asked the same question for the millionth time

shortDefinitions: constituting unspecified but very large number in sequence

definitions: each of one million equal parts into which something is or may be divided

examples.text: a dot less than a millionth of an inch in diameter

shortDefinitions: each of one million equal parts into which something is or may be divided
